cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of missing data in machine learning, specifically in the context of multi-modal segmentation of medical images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes modifications to the standard 3D UNet architecture, which involves training schemes, multi-pathway architecture, and pre-training of pathways, indicating that it may also fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks in the proposed method suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with multi-modal segmentation, which is a subfield of medical imaging, indicating that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
